About me

Hi there folks! My (full) name is Juan Camilo Sanchez Arias. Seems long, eh? Thats because of my Afro-Latinx background and how surnames work for us Hispanics (you can learn more about it here). I was born in Cali (Colombia), the most calidosa city and capital of salsa. Im a Normal High School Graduate, Doctor of Medicine from Universdiad del Valle School of Medicine (2007-2014), and I recently defended my PhD in Neuroscience at the University of Victoria (2015-2020).

Im all about biomedical research (specially that dealing with neuronal networks and molecular mechanisms of synaptic transmission), translational research, science communication, and evidence-based medicine.
Me giving one of the 4 NB Gulila Star Award talks at IGJC2019 The other part of the award was a 3D printed connexin model!

Ive started to merge my techy hobbies with my science and medicine curiosity. This led me to a path to learn R and this space (originally discussed during a lab meeting). So, basically R Jam Sessions is a little nook in the internet of things with data science and data visualization content for beginners using datasets from topics close to my research interests, others dear to my heart (hi homesickness? how you doing?), and some others Ive come across purely by chance.

As a beginner, my code is not the prettiest nor the most efficient and Im always receptive to constructive feedback. So dont hesitate in reaching out through issues or Twitter @juan_sanar to drop tips, advice, or words of encouragement.
